# Pinned sha256 baseline for the on-box "source of truth" agent-browser
# SKILL.md this skill's own SKILL.md defers to when present:
#   ~/clawd/skills/agent-browser/SKILL.md
# (see 03-agent-browser/SKILL.md — "If that path exists, treat it as the
# source of truth.")
#
# That file lives OUTSIDE this repo and is box-local, so it cannot be
# byte-diffed against on-disk repo source the way agent-browser.skill's four
# packaged docs are (lib-archive-diff.sh). Instead this is a PINNED baseline:
# captured explicitly, once, by scripts/pin-onbox-source-of-truth.sh — never
# auto-updated, never captured silently as a side effect of a QC run.
#
# UNCAPTURED = no baseline has ever been recorded on this box. qc-agent-
# browser.sh treats that as a FAIL (fail-closed — an unknown state is a gap
# to close, not a silent pass), naming the exact fix: run
# `scripts/pin-onbox-source-of-truth.sh` once the on-box copy is reviewed and
# accepted as known-good.
#
# Format once captured: <sha256>  <byte-count>  <captured-date>
UNCAPTURED
